bug.short_desc: Refresh problem in qx.ui.mobile.form.List when model sorted

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1217 Sample project of the issue
On a qx.ui.form.List object, if the the model (qx.data.Array) is sorted, the display of the List become corrupt.
It's difficult to explain the exact effect but I have a sample of the issue in attachment.
Thanks you very much. I guess you are talking about the mobile list and not the list in the qx.ui.form namespace, right?

I fixed the problem in qx.Mobile List by listening to "change" event, too of qx.data.Array. This event also contains information about the type of change like "add", "remove","sort".
Everytime, one of these changed event types occur, I re-render the whole list.
